<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-100-062 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 035 743</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  July 29 1991 v25 n30 p21(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Why IS needs to watch AI. (information systems, artificialintelligence)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hayes, Pat.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information systems (IS) departments are advised to pay attentionto the emergence of artificial intelligence (AI) as a keytechnology for the 1990s.andP;  AI is increasingly important because itis an effective technology to manage the huge increase ininformation generated by other computer industry technologies,such as fiber-based networks.andP;  AI is critical because there isjust too much information to be managed by traditional methods.andO;There is also a shortage of qualified expert humans to analyzeinformation, and systems are becoming too complicated to bemanaged by traditional computers.andP;  Numerous companies arediscovering the benefits of applying AI to numerous arenas,including expense account auditing, production scheduling andcustomer service.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Artificial intelligenceInformation systemsHigh TechnologyManagement of EDPOutlookComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>